article.headline: Arkansas 86, Centenary 52
article.story:
FAYETTEVILLE, Ark. (AP) -- Ruby Vaden scored 18 points as
Arkansas used 41 turnovers and a school-record 28 steals to defeat
Centenary 86-52 on Sunday.

The Lady Razorbacks (2-0) came close to breaking the
one-game-old record set Friday when Arkansas created 45 turnovers
from Alabama State. They scored an unofficial record 43 points from
the 41 turnovers Sunday.

For Centenary (1-1), Laura Kizyte led with 16 points.

Arkansas was up 51-25 at the half.

Sheree Thompson grabbed a career high eight steals while Kristin
Peoples added a career-tying six. The steal record dated back to
the first season of conference play at Arkansas when the Lady
Razorbacks forced 26 steals from Texas Christian on Jan. 11, 1983.

Rochelle Vaughn added 16 points and April Seggebruch rounded out
the double-digit scorers with 10 for Arkansas.
